---
unit: 1
unitTitle: Introduction
title: "Unit 1: Introduction — Demo Course"
description: "A template unit demonstrating all available course activity components."
quote: "&ldquo;The more that you read, the more things you will know.&rdquo; &mdash; Dr. Seuss"
objectives:
  - Understand the structure and purpose of a course unit page
  - Identify the core activity types available in the template
  - Use the accordion, quiz, audio, video, and tab components correctly
---

{% from "macros/course.njk" import activitySection, reviewSection,
   accordion, audioPlayer, videoEmbed, quizMC, tabSet %}


{# ══ Activity 1 — Reading / Introduction ═════════════════════════════ #}

{% call activitySection(1, "Introduction", "book") %}
<p>
  Welcome to Unit 1. This page is a <strong>template</strong> showing all the
  standard activity components available for building course units. Replace the
  placeholder content with your own material.
</p>
<p>
  Each activity is wrapped in a numbered card. The objectives above are driven
  by the <code>objectives</code> list in the page frontmatter — no HTML needed.
</p>
{% endcall %}


{# ══ Activity 2 — Accordion (Q&A reveal) ════════════════════════════ #}

{% call activitySection(2, "Key Questions", "chat-left-text") %}
<p class="mb-3">
  Expand each question and think about your answer before reading the response.
</p>
<div class="accordion" id="unit01-accordion">

  {% call accordion("acc-01-a", "What is the main purpose of this activity type?") %}
  <p>
    Accordion reveals encourage learners to actively recall an answer before
    reading the explanation. They work well for vocabulary, definitions, and
    reflective questions.
  </p>
  {% endcall %}

  {% call accordion("acc-01-b", "When should you use a tab set instead of an accordion?") %}
  <p>
    Use tabs when the content options are roughly equal in length and the learner
    should easily switch between them for comparison. Use accordions when the
    items are sequential or when you want only one item visible at a time.
  </p>
  {% endcall %}

  {% call accordion("acc-01-c", "Can accordion items contain formatted content?") %}
  <p>
    Yes — the accordion body accepts any HTML. You can include lists, code
    blocks, images, or even nested activity components.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Lists work fine</li>
    <li>So does <strong>bold</strong> and <em>italic</em> text</li>
  </ul>
  {% endcall %}

</div>
{% endcall %}


{# ══ Activity 3 — Audio player ═══════════════════════════════════════ #}

{% call activitySection(3, "Listening", "headphones") %}
<p class="mb-3">
  Listen to the audio and make notes on the key points raised.
</p>
{{ audioPlayer("/assets/audio/placeholder.mp3", "Tutor introduction — approx. 2 minutes") }}
<div class="mt-3">
  <p class="small" style="color:#e0e0e0;">
    <i class="bi bi-info-circle"></i>
    Replace the <code>src</code> path with the real audio file.
    The second argument is the caption shown below the player.
  </p>
</div>
{% endcall %}


{# ══ Activity 4 — Multiple-choice quiz ══════════════════════════════ #}

{% call activitySection(4, "Check Your Understanding", "patch-question") %}
<p class="mb-3">Select the best answer for each question.</p>

{% call quizMC("quiz-01-a", "Which component should you use for sequential Q&A reveals?", 1,
   "Accordions are designed for sequential, one-at-a-time reveals. Tabs are better for parallel comparisons.") %}
  <label class="quiz-option">
    <input type="radio" name="quiz-01-a" value="0"> Tab set
  </label>
  <label class="quiz-option">
    <input type="radio" name="quiz-01-a" value="1"> Accordion
  </label>
  <label class="quiz-option">
    <input type="radio" name="quiz-01-a" value="2"> Audio player
  </label>
  <label class="quiz-option">
    <input type="radio" name="quiz-01-a" value="3"> Video embed
  </label>
{% endcall %}

<div class="mt-4">
{% call quizMC("quiz-01-b", "Where are the learning objectives defined for a unit page?", 0,
   "Objectives are listed in the page frontmatter as a YAML array, so no HTML markup is needed in the unit file.") %}
  <label class="quiz-option">
    <input type="radio" name="quiz-01-b" value="0"> In the page frontmatter as a YAML list
  </label>
  <label class="quiz-option">
    <input type="radio" name="quiz-01-b" value="1"> Hardcoded in the course-unit layout
  </label>
  <label class="quiz-option">
    <input type="radio" name="quiz-01-b" value="2"> In a separate data file for each unit
  </label>
{% endcall %}
</div>
{% endcall %}


{# ══ Activity 5 — Tabbed content ════════════════════════════════════ #}

{% set strategyTabs = [
  {id: "why",      label: "Why"},
  {id: "how",      label: "How"},
  {id: "example",  label: "Example"}
] %}

{% call activitySection(5, "Approaches", "layout-text-sidebar") %}
<p class="mb-3">
  Tabs work well when presenting parallel views of the same topic — such as
  why, how, and a worked example.
</p>

{% call tabSet("unit01-tabs", strategyTabs) %}
  <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="unit01-tabs-why" role="tabpanel">
    <p>
      Explain the <strong>purpose</strong> or motivation for the concept.
      Why does it matter? What problem does it solve?
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="tab-pane fade" id="unit01-tabs-how" role="tabpanel">
    <p>
      Describe <strong>how</strong> it works — the steps, rules, or process
      involved. Use numbered lists or code blocks where appropriate.
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>Step one</li>
      <li>Step two</li>
      <li>Step three</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
  <div class="tab-pane fade" id="unit01-tabs-example" role="tabpanel">
    <p>
      Provide a <strong>concrete example</strong>. Show input and output,
      or walk through the steps with real data.
    </p>
    <code>input → process → output</code>
  </div>
{% endcall %}

{% endcall %}


{# ══ Activity 6 — Video embed ════════════════════════════════════════ #}

{% call activitySection(6, "Watch", "play-circle") %}
<p class="mb-3">Watch the video and answer the reflection question below.</p>
{{ videoEmbed("dQw4w9WgXcQ", "Replace this YouTube ID with the real video. Caption is optional.") }}
<div class="mt-3 p-3" style="background:#333; border-radius:0.375rem;">
  <p class="mb-1 fw-semibold">Reflection</p>
  <p class="mb-0 small" style="color:#e0e0e0;">
    After watching, write 2–3 sentences summarising the main point in your own words.
  </p>
</div>
{% endcall %}


{# ══ Review ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}

{% call reviewSection() %}
<p>
  Use this section for end-of-unit self-assessment. You can place additional
  quiz components here, a summary accordion, or a reflective writing prompt.
</p>

<div class="accordion mt-3" id="unit01-review-accordion">
  {% call accordion("rev-01-a", "Summary: What are the core activity types in this template?") %}
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Accordion</strong> — Q&amp;A reveals, definitions, guided reflection</li>
    <li><strong>Audio player</strong> — listening tasks, tutor introductions</li>
    <li><strong>Video embed</strong> — YouTube lectures or demonstrations</li>
    <li><strong>Multiple-choice quiz</strong> — comprehension checks with instant feedback</li>
    <li><strong>Tab set</strong> — parallel views (why / how / example)</li>
  </ul>
  {% endcall %}
</div>

<p class="mt-3 small" style="color:#e0e0e0;">
  <i class="bi bi-arrow-right-circle"></i>
  Proceed to <a href="{{ (courseBaseUrl + '/unit-02') | url }}">Unit 2</a> when ready.
</p>
{% endcall %}
